5147,Ad-Lib,[],['Word Game'],"Unlike Spill and Spell, this game is extremely similar to Scrabble, differing in only one small regard.<br/><br/>The game concept is that the point values are on the board instead of the letter tiles. This supposedly permits a more liberal use of the letters and helps develop full word power and effective strategy.<br/><br/>Besides that major departure from Scrabble, there are a number of minor differences, such as the number of tiles held on the rack, and the bonus for using all tiles.<br/><br/>",1970,,,
5148,Triani,[],['Card Game'],"The object of Triani is to draw and capture cards that enable a player to outscore opponents in &quot;booking&quot; his section of the playing board. 1 &quot;book&quot; consists of three cards of any suit; the sum being the same as the point value above a card outline on the board. A player may double his score by forming a &quot;book&quot; of three cards of his suit. Quick climaxes with unpredictable outcome till the last, as players strive to obtain the high value &quot;TRIANI BONUS SCORE&quot; (Joker and two Aces in their suit).<br/><br/>Triani is played with a special board, but normal decks of cards, the exact number determined by the number of people playing (1-2 decks plus Jokers).<br/><br/>",1957,,,
5149,Bedlam,['Trading'],"['Negotiation', 'Real-time']","Pit with a board.<br/><br/>In this game, the objective is to move along your pawn's lane from one end of the board and back before anyone else does.  Along that path are 8 different pictures, repeated over and over, and each person's path is slightly different (at least the sequence of the images varies, but the same images are used).<br/><br/>Each player also holds a hand of cards and their goal is to collect cards with the same images as the one their pawn is resting on.  That part of the game is pretty much the same as the classic game, Pit.  Players trade cards unseen, in any combinations (unlike Pit) and all that must happen is that an equal number of cards must be given and taken.<br/><br/>When the timer runs out, move your pawn forward the number of spaces equal to the number of matching cards in your hand.  At that point, most of the time, you will be sitting on a different image, so another round of trading is necessary to redistribute your hand.<br/><br/>",1995,,,
