5270,Maestria,"['Pattern Building', 'Real-Time', 'Tile Placement']",['Word Game'],"A strange word game, where each player draws from a bag 39 tiles with geometric segments on them.  Simultaneously, both players try to arrange their tiles to make a word of four or more letters (most letters are 2x3 tiles, the &quot;I&quot; is 1x3, &quot;M&quot;, &quot;T&quot;, &quot;W&quot;and &quot;Y&quot; are 3x3).  First player to shout Stop! wins the round and scores.  The word may be contested.<br/><br/>Note that a word with an &quot;I&quot; in it will score less, and conversely with &quot;M&quot;, &quot;T&quot;, &quot;W&quot; or &quot;Y&quot;.<br/><br/>The players swap boards and shuffle the tiles of each board around, then play repeats.  On the second round, swap again but draw 6 more tiles.  Words must now be 5+ letters.  Repeat for a third round (six-letter words), drawing six tiles again, so there are six words scored total in a game.  The boards show bonuses that can be scored by making really long words.<br/><br/>The rules show the exact patterns that make up each letter.  An incorrectly drawn letter will lose a challenge.<br/><br/>",1991,,,
