9898,Tic Tac Toe Times 10,"['Area-Impulse', 'Pattern Building', 'Tile Placement']",['Abstract Strategy'],"The playing board consists of nine individual games of Tic Tac Toe which are played with small cards.  However, each of these nine games is in itself a square within one Master Game.  Thus, when a player wins an individual game, he or she will also be winning one of the large squares in the 10th or Master Game.<br/><br/><br/>In Tic Tac Toe Times 10 each cell of the 3x3 grid of the master-game is broken into a 3x3 grid for a mini-game of Tic-Tac-Toe. You play each mini-game of  Tic-Tac-Toe normally to try and win that cell in the Master grid.<br/><br/>There is a twist to normal Tic-Tac-Toe play however. The first player can place their piece in any of the 91 min-board squares on the board. After that each player must move to the mini-game which their opponent sends them.<br/><br/><br/>    So if the first player plays in the top right square of one of the 9 mini-games, then the opponent must play their move in the minigame in the top right Master cell. Subsequent play follows the same rule. <br/><br/><br/><br/>    There are two exceptions to this however for which you get an open turn and you may place your piece on any tile you like.<br/><br/><br/><br/>        Your opponent sends you to a tile that has already been won (either by you or them).<br/>        Your opponent sends you to a tile which is full, and hence a tie. <br/>    <br/><br/><br/>Winning Condition<br/><br/>The first player to win 3 cells in a row in the Master game wins.<br/><br/>Contents:<br/>Playing board<br/>39 small &quot;X&quot;<br/>39 small &quot;O&quot;<br/>9 large &quot;X&quot;<br/>9 Large &quot;O&quot;<br/>(Instructions printed in boxtop)<br/><br/>",1977,,,
